      <h2>Our Philosophy</h2>
      <hr>
    <!-- </div> -->
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
        <div class="about-text">

          <p>Nothing is more precious than your memories. Memories are what makes you: you. If time is all you have left, your memories are what you did with your time. And yet it is easy to neglect and to forget your memories, letting them fade away.</p>

          <p><i>“We do not remember days, we remember moments.”</i> Cesare Pavese, Italian poet</p>

          <p>In essence, our philosophy revolves around the existential crisis caused by our loss of memories. With Pikaday, you can turn your favourite moments into meaningful memories.</p>
 
          <p>Pikaday is a way to remember your memories simply by collecting one picture a day of the moment that you consider the most important of that day. Pikaday is not just another ‘app’ or ‘social media’. Instead, we want to take the first &amp feasible step in solving the problem that experiences are easily forgotten. In essence, we value memories above all. Although it may be hard to pick the most valuable picture of the day in thirty years; you will have 365 memories of this entire year. This forces users like you to actively reflect on your daily experiences and prioritising the picture that best reflects the day.</p>

          <p>With Pikaday, we want you to be able to pleasantly take, collect and rediscover your memories through your own personal collection of pictures.
          Conserve the past, picture the present and expect anything from the future. Save one memory a day and bring your story to life with Pikaday.</p>

          <p>Save a pik a day with Pikaday

          </p>
          <br><br><br>
        </div>
